<i>How is business doing?!</i>

31
00:01:29,242 --> 00:01:31,471
<i>Well enough, I'd say.</i>

32
00:01:31,734 --> 00:01:34,654
~ SHINYA SHOKUDO ~
Midnight Restaurant

33
00:01:34,654 --> 00:01:40,246
<i>(*Rice with tea and toppings)</i>
Episode 3
Ochazuke*

34
00:01:44,141 --> 00:01:46,154
- Thanks for that.
- Thanks.

35
00:01:57,008 --> 00:01:59,659
Master... More natto*.
(*fermented soy beans)

36
00:01:59,690 --> 00:02:01,050
Coming.

37
00:02:02,734 --> 00:02:04,344
You know, Master?

38
00:02:04,438 --> 00:02:07,339
These days you
don't seem to come by.

39
00:02:07,777 --> 00:02:10,689
Ahh... Is that right?

40
00:02:11,107 --> 00:02:13,660
Next time, I'll come.

41
00:02:13,843 --> 00:02:16,383
You said the
same exact thing last time.

42
00:02:16,837 --> 00:02:18,431
Sorry.

43
00:02:18,461 --> 00:02:20,645
This time, I mean it.

44
00:02:20,932 --> 00:02:22,989
Should I believe that?

45
00:02:23,355 --> 00:02:25,112
Adults are bad, aren't they?

46
00:02:25,137 --> 00:02:27,205
<i>- Her name is Jun-chan.
- Like Master would have the time...</i>

47
00:02:27,230 --> 00:02:32,010
<i>(*Character from a famous manga
by Yamato Waki)</i>
<i>She is a new-half (transgender) running
a gay-bar called Murasaki no Ue*.</i>

48
00:02:32,458 --> 00:02:34,509
<i>Sharing her partner
Yoshida-kun's love for natto,</i>

49
00:02:34,534 --> 00:02:37,509
<i>the two started
dating because of that.</i>

50
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:38,807
By the way...

51
00:02:38,929 --> 00:02:40,550
You'll stay over tonight, right?

52
00:02:40,615 --> 00:02:44,139
Ahh... Sorry.
I have a meeting early in the morning.

53
00:02:44,408 --> 00:02:48,268
Uh?! Even if you
have one, it's okay!

54
00:02:48,768 --> 00:02:51,337
Just stay!

55
00:02:51,362 --> 00:02:52,807
Stop pushing it...

56
00:02:52,862 --> 00:02:54,284
Come on.

57
00:02:54,866 --> 00:02:56,944
All right.
As you wish.

58
00:02:57,100 --> 00:02:58,878
Awesome!

59
00:03:18,372 --> 00:03:22,053
<i>Since the joys of the
palate transcend gender...</i>

60
00:03:22,078 --> 00:03:24,780
<i>you really never know.</i>

61
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:34,461
Here you go.

62
00:03:34,629 --> 00:03:36,326
Thanks.

63
00:03:56,409 --> 00:03:57,558
<i>Anyhow...</i>

64
00:03:57,620 --> 00:04:01,213
<i>Let's leave Jun-chan's story at that.</i>

65
00:04:03,112 --> 00:04:04,206
Come on in!

66
00:04:04,231 --> 00:04:06,814
<i>Our protagonists tonight
are these three ladies.</i>

67
00:04:06,839 --> 00:04:07,905
Ume.

68
00:04:07,930 --> 00:04:10,188
- Salmon.
- Tarako.

69
00:04:10,391 --> 00:04:11,521
Coming.

70
00:04:11,622 --> 00:04:13,972
<i>They are known here...</i>

71
00:04:14,203 --> 00:04:17,369
<i>as the "Ochazuke Sisters."</i>

72
00:04:26,861 --> 00:04:29,377
Here you go, ume is ready.

73
00:04:31,455 --> 00:04:33,761
<i>Bon apetit!</i>

74
00:04:38,324 --> 00:04:40,784
Yukari... Did she really
want marriage that bad?

75
00:04:40,913 --> 00:04:42,836
Maybe she had enough of her job?!

76
00:04:43,020 --> 00:04:45,092
He's eight years older,
for God's sake!

77
00:04:45,139 --> 00:04:47,206
- Have you seen his hairline?
- Right...

78
00:04:47,238 --> 00:04:48,890
<i>(*middle-aged man)</i>
Already oyaji* material, all right.

79
00:04:48,915 --> 00:04:50,519
If I really must tie the knot,

80
00:04:50,643 --> 00:04:52,307
it'll only be with
someone ten years younger.

81
00:04:52,612 --> 00:04:54,468
Right?!

82
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:59,579
They must be back
from the wedding party.

83
00:04:59,667 --> 00:05:01,789
Quite a sight, isn't?

84
00:05:01,917 --> 00:05:04,597
Grown ass women eating ochazuke,
bloated mug and all.

85
00:05:04,622 --> 00:05:06,031
They'll hear you!

86
00:05:06,222 --> 00:05:08,808
The hell I care?

87
00:05:11,387 --> 00:05:13,288
Thanks for that.

88
00:05:13,448 --> 00:05:16,619
- Tarako is the best.
- Ume is number one!
- Salmon is the way!

89
00:05:16,644 --> 00:05:18,528
The ume's unique delicacy...

90
00:05:18,553 --> 00:05:21,316
The perfect harmony of salmon and rice...

91
00:05:21,341 --> 00:05:22,354
Tarako is no joke, either.

92
00:05:22,379 --> 00:05:24,380
It's ochazuke, all right!

93
00:05:24,503 --> 00:05:26,146
Right?!

94
00:05:27,392 --> 00:05:30,328
On that note, wasn't
today's menu just a mess?

95
00:05:30,353 --> 00:05:31,407
It was horrible.

96
00:05:31,432 --> 00:05:33,682
They serve you those
tiny Hors d'oeuvre...

97
00:05:33,707 --> 00:05:35,650
- It didn't even feel like eating.
- Right.

98
00:05:35,675 --> 00:05:40,268
We sure packed those envelopes,
and look at what we get.

99
00:05:41,389 --> 00:05:45,099
This is why weddings are the worst.

100
00:05:45,124 --> 00:05:47,457
Right?!

101
00:05:55,142 --> 00:05:57,627
Still, you know...

102
00:05:57,652 --> 00:05:59,914
Yukari sure was pretty.

103
00:06:01,817 --> 00:06:03,500
Yeah.

104
00:06:03,525 --> 00:06:06,956
I've never seen
anyone so happy before.

105
00:06:08,252 --> 00:06:13,340
So she indeed must be happy?!

106
00:06:13,365 --> 00:06:15,989
She has to be...

107
00:06:16,115 --> 00:06:18,580
Of course she is.

108
00:06:21,239 --> 00:06:22,908
Next time.

109
00:06:23,272 --> 00:06:26,216
Should we go to an
omiai (marriage meeting) party?

110
00:06:26,384 --> 00:06:28,306
- Omiai party?
- Yeah.

111
00:06:28,358 --> 00:06:31,806
This colleague of mine
has gone to a few already.

112
00:06:31,843 --> 00:06:33,371
So what kind of people you meet?

113
00:06:33,544 --> 00:06:35,555
Well...

114
00:06:36,039 --> 00:06:40,002
But, I hear that these days
you can meet a lot of younger men.

115
00:06:40,054 --> 00:06:41,770
- Really?
- Yeah.

116
00:06:42,483 --> 00:06:45,246
Omiai party...

117
00:06:46,165 --> 00:06:48,019
You two!

118
00:06:48,478 --> 00:06:51,991
Have you listened to what kind
of nonsense you're prattling about?

119
00:06:52,070 --> 00:06:54,238
Omiai party?!
The hell is that?

120
00:06:54,288 --> 00:06:55,915
How can you compromise so cheaply?

121
00:06:56,002 --> 00:06:57,810
- Still...
- Listen.

122
00:06:57,906 --> 00:07:00,319
We pursue true love!

123
00:07:00,432 --> 00:07:03,119
The great romances
you see on the big screen!

124
00:07:03,243 --> 00:07:05,994
How can you just give up now?

125
00:07:06,291 --> 00:07:08,007
I... guess so?!

126
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:09,669
Sure.

127
00:07:09,869 --> 00:07:11,616
Pretty Woman!

128
00:07:11,641 --> 00:07:14,294
Forever seeking the true romance!

129
00:07:14,619 --> 00:07:15,992
Right!

130
00:07:16,055 --> 00:07:18,519
<i>(*short for Kekkon
katsudo, seeking marriage)</i>
- Konkatsu*?!
- The hell with that!

131
00:07:18,751 --> 00:07:21,298
- Omiai?
- Forget about it.

132
00:07:21,325 --> 00:07:23,464
We accept no compromise.
True romance!

133
00:07:24,157 --> 00:07:25,573
True romance!

134
00:07:25,645 --> 00:07:28,113
Our Prince Charming
is out there for sure!

135
00:07:29,091 --> 00:07:31,083
Right?!

136
00:07:32,469 --> 00:07:33,404
Master.

137
00:07:33,475 --> 00:07:34,763
Another serving of ume.

138
00:07:34,860 --> 00:07:36,357
- Salmon!
- Tarako.

139
00:07:39,475 --> 00:07:40,503
Coming.

140
00:07:44,741 --> 00:07:49,591
<i>Same time and same company,
they drop by, and then...</i>

141
00:07:50,445 --> 00:07:51,663
Ume.

142
00:07:51,688 --> 00:07:53,877
- Salmon.
- Tarako.

143
00:07:57,608 --> 00:07:59,224
<i>Enjoying their ochazuke,</i>

144
00:07:59,388 --> 00:08:01,568
<i>they always talk about men.</i>

145
00:08:01,593 --> 00:08:04,435
- So we drank all night together.
- Really?

146
00:08:04,435 --> 00:08:07,560
Aren't those two a
little on the cute side?

147
00:08:08,008 --> 00:08:09,943
Cute.

148
00:08:10,138 --> 00:08:12,372
Go have a word with them.

149
00:08:12,864 --> 00:08:14,244
Give it a rest.

150
00:08:14,269 --> 00:08:17,724
Only a cheapskate would
come to a place like this.

151
00:08:18,752 --> 00:08:20,439
Guess so?!

152
00:08:24,936 --> 00:08:26,465
Sorry.

153
00:08:35,474 --> 00:08:39,474
It was about....
three months later?

154
00:08:49,892 --> 00:08:50,836
Ume.

155
00:08:51,172 --> 00:08:52,042
Salmon.

156
00:08:52,682 --> 00:08:54,262
Ohh?!

157
00:08:54,704 --> 00:08:55,945
How about the other,

158
00:08:56,157 --> 00:08:57,405
the one always ordering Tarako?

159
00:08:57,594 --> 00:08:59,496
Said her mother is sick,

160
00:08:59,645 --> 00:09:01,637
so she had to go to
Kyushu and tend to her.

161
00:09:01,761 --> 00:09:03,271
I see.

162
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:05,280
Not just that, I'm afraid.

163
00:09:05,533 --> 00:09:06,585
Uh?!

164
00:09:06,916 --> 00:09:08,115
Rumi...

165
00:09:08,342 --> 00:09:11,302
The brat's going there
for an omiai as well!

166
00:09:11,982 --> 00:09:14,052
Say what?!

167
00:09:14,077 --> 00:09:17,177
Not to mention,
with someone ten years older.

168
00:09:17,420 --> 00:09:18,683
Uh?!

169
00:09:19,050 --> 00:09:20,113
Yeah!

170
00:09:21,644 --> 00:09:22,707
Omiai...

171
00:09:23,488 --> 00:09:24,347
in Kyushu?!

172
00:09:24,622 --> 00:09:26,489
Yeah.

173
00:09:27,114 --> 00:09:29,388
My mom is sick,

174
00:09:29,466 --> 00:09:31,568
so I want to reassure her quickly.

175
00:09:31,795 --> 00:09:33,154
- Really?!
- Yeah.

176
00:09:33,687 --> 00:09:38,804
I just want to get married.

177
00:09:39,835 --> 00:09:43,788
Because I'm the only child.

178
00:09:44,507 --> 00:09:45,507
Really?!

179
00:09:46,525 --> 00:09:48,024
Ha ha ha...

180
00:09:48,851 --> 00:09:50,070
Best wishes!

181
00:09:52,792 --> 00:09:54,682
Traitor!

182
00:10:03,497 --> 00:10:05,044
I haven't contacted you since then.

183
00:10:05,349 --> 00:10:06,349
Really.

184
00:10:06,798 --> 00:10:07,798
That brat...

185
00:10:08,357 --> 00:10:10,587
She's using her mother as an excuse,

186
00:10:10,669 --> 00:10:12,940
but she was just feeling lonely.

187
00:10:13,013 --> 00:10:16,272
Hmph! The same one who
always despised older men?!

188
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,810
It's a compromise, all right.

189
00:10:17,965 --> 00:10:21,525
The brat gave up on true romance.

190
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:25,540
Ahhh... Drives me crazy!

191
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:27,688
She's done with us.
I'm never calling her again!

192
00:10:27,738 --> 00:10:28,632
It's betrayal.

193
00:10:28,694 --> 00:10:32,204
As vile as betrayals can get!

194
00:10:33,702 --> 00:10:34,560
Master...

195
00:10:34,755 --> 00:10:37,615
- Where is our ochazuke?
- Let's get moving!

196
00:10:37,933 --> 00:10:40,221
<i>I certainly feel what you're saying,</i>

197
00:10:40,347 --> 00:10:43,097
<i>but don't take it all out on me.</i>

198
00:10:44,580 --> 00:10:48,830
<i>The two remained
on good terms for a while.</i>

199
00:10:49,770 --> 00:10:53,825
<i>When our "Ume Sister" Miki-chan
was hospitalized for ob-gyn matters...</i>

200
00:10:53,944 --> 00:10:55,604
Wow... Really?!

201
00:10:55,710 --> 00:11:00,343
<i>Seems like "Salmon Sister" Kana-chan
was always by her side.</i>

202
00:11:00,589 --> 00:11:03,989
I wanted to have this so much!

203
00:11:04,802 --> 00:11:08,112
- Congrats on your recovery.
- Thanks!

204
00:11:11,567 --> 00:11:13,377
All thanks to you.

205
00:11:13,413 --> 00:11:15,133
I'm just glad you got better.

206
00:11:15,380 --> 00:11:17,025
Hope I can keep counting on you.

207
00:11:17,135 --> 00:11:18,169
Same goes for me.

208
00:11:18,245 --> 00:11:19,365
From here on in,

209
00:11:19,445 --> 00:11:21,225
Kana, you're
the only one for me!

210
00:11:21,299 --> 00:11:23,139
Miki...

211
00:11:25,972 --> 00:11:28,571
- Konkatsu?!
- The hell with it.

212
00:11:28,596 --> 00:11:30,746
- Omiai?!
- Gimme a break.

213
00:11:30,832 --> 00:11:33,039
No compromise.

214
00:11:33,870 --> 00:11:35,239
For sure.

215
00:11:35,264 --> 00:11:37,505
Pure love is in the air.

216
00:11:37,770 --> 00:11:39,083
Right?!

217
00:11:39,108 --> 00:11:42,586
<i>People say that
women can't be friends,</i>

218
00:11:42,810 --> 00:11:45,920
<i>but I always thought it
wasn't the case for these two.</i>

219
00:11:47,420 --> 00:11:49,630
<i>Yet...</i>

220
00:11:52,968 --> 00:11:54,246
By the way, Master.

221
00:11:54,365 --> 00:11:57,355
Are the Ochazuke Sisters
coming by, these days?

222
00:11:58,050 --> 00:11:59,816
Now that I think about it,

223
00:11:59,950 --> 00:12:01,970
I haven't seen them
in quite a while?!

224
00:12:02,050 --> 00:12:04,120
- Told you.
- Yeah.

225
00:12:04,644 --> 00:12:06,074
Uh?!

226
00:12:06,304 --> 00:12:07,665
This other day...

227
00:12:07,690 --> 00:12:10,600
They made a scene at my bar.

228
00:12:10,710 --> 00:12:14,640
Seems like Salmon Sister is
going out with Ume Sister's ex.

229
00:12:14,740 --> 00:12:16,750
Uh?!

230
00:12:17,045 --> 00:12:19,155
<i>According to her,
seems like the two...</i>

231
00:12:19,180 --> 00:12:23,060
<i>had been frequenting
her bar pretty often.</i>

232
00:12:26,225 --> 00:12:29,775
Break it up with Mitsuhiko,
or you'll regret it.

233
00:12:29,944 --> 00:12:32,373
Like you care?
Just let me be.

234
00:12:32,494 --> 00:12:34,894
Of course I care.

235
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:37,520
What are you, jealous?

236
00:12:38,711 --> 00:12:39,950
Uh?!

237
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:42,830
You're just jealous, it's obvious.

238
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:45,874
The hell are you prattling about?
Why would I?

239
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:47,780
Why would you...

240
00:12:47,898 --> 00:12:50,975
Listen, why should
I ever be jealous?

241
00:12:51,006 --> 00:12:52,660
Let me think...

242
00:12:52,726 --> 00:12:54,140
Enough with that.

243
00:12:54,295 --> 00:12:56,203
I'm just telling you for your sake.

244
00:12:56,228 --> 00:12:59,030
And why don't you
mind your own business?

245
00:12:59,182 --> 00:13:01,462
As if you were the
one who dumped him first...

246
00:13:03,941 --> 00:13:05,680
What is this?

247
00:13:05,904 --> 00:13:07,454
Makes you feel uneasy, I bet?

248
00:13:07,570 --> 00:13:10,547
Seeing me experience true love.

249
00:13:23,090 --> 00:13:24,640
The hell are you doing?

250
00:13:24,679 --> 00:13:27,274
Let go!
What are you doing?

251
00:13:29,432 --> 00:13:31,352
Excuse me... Ladies...

252
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:34,230
Don't do this... Don't!

253
00:13:35,317 --> 00:13:36,976
Please stop.

254
00:13:43,437 --> 00:13:45,087
You fucker!

255
00:13:46,741 --> 00:13:48,891
What the hell are you doing?

256
00:13:59,828 --> 00:14:03,178
Shut the fuck up,
you sons of bitches!

257
00:14:12,530 --> 00:14:15,960
So there's no friendship
between women, indeed.

258
00:14:17,477 --> 00:14:19,217
None.

259
00:14:19,327 --> 00:14:22,097
As long as men continue to exist.

260
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:27,260
That's sad to hear.

261
00:14:32,835 --> 00:14:38,352
<i>"The kiddo felt dizzy,</i>

262
00:14:38,376 --> 00:14:43,635
<i>but desperately kept hanging on."</i>

263
00:14:44,023 --> 00:14:49,023
<i>"This waltz is no
laughing matter, either."</i>

264
00:14:49,671 --> 00:14:54,671
<i>"So she pranced around the
kitchen as if she went batty,"</i>

265
00:14:55,136 --> 00:14:56,214
<i>"making the cupboard shake
left and right, and making a mess."</i>

266
00:14:56,214 --> 00:14:57,824
Any hobbies?
<i>"making the cupboard shake
left and right, and making a mess."</i>

267
00:14:57,824 --> 00:14:59,785
<i>"making the cupboard shake
left and right, and making a mess."</i>

268
00:14:59,785 --> 00:15:00,519
I do some ballroom dancing,
every now and then.
<i>"making the cupboard shake
left and right, and making a mess."</i>

269
00:15:00,519 --> 00:15:02,663
I do some ballroom dancing,
every now and then.
<i>"An ice cold stare was
stamped on her mother's face"</i>

270
00:15:02,663 --> 00:15:04,523
<i>"An ice cold stare was
stamped on her mother's face"</i>

271
00:15:04,523 --> 00:15:06,477
Is... that so?!
<i>"An ice cold stare was
stamped on her mother's face"</i>

272
00:15:06,477 --> 00:15:08,120
Yes.
<i>"An ice cold stare was
stamped on her mother's face"</i>

273
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:11,416
<i>"An ice cold stare was
stamped on her mother's face"</i>

274
00:15:37,220 --> 00:15:39,460
If you look back at the
history of ballroom dancing,

275
00:15:39,470 --> 00:15:42,710
you'll inevitably go
back to its roots in waltz.

276
00:15:44,334 --> 00:15:46,589
There's this theory that it
all started in the Provence area,

277
00:15:46,614 --> 00:15:50,382
with a dance called "volt."

278
00:15:57,126 --> 00:15:58,846
Our Prince Charming is out there!

279
00:15:59,992 --> 00:16:01,512
Right?!

280
00:16:05,736 --> 00:16:10,413
<i>"You brought me to bed,"</i>

281
00:16:10,960 --> 00:16:15,868
<i>"as I was still hanging onto you,"</i>

282
00:16:16,337 --> 00:16:20,564
<i>"while dancing the waltz."</i>

283
00:16:33,026 --> 00:16:35,506
Tastes like crap.

284
00:16:49,304 --> 00:16:50,804
Come on in.

285
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:55,510
Ume.

286
00:16:58,977 --> 00:17:00,837
Coming.

287
00:17:04,678 --> 00:17:07,186
In the end,
finally decimated to one,

288
00:17:07,211 --> 00:17:09,441
our Ochazuke Sisters.

289
00:17:30,405 --> 00:17:34,135
You know, at this age.

290
00:17:36,976 --> 00:17:39,733
How should I put it.

291
00:17:39,991 --> 00:17:44,145
You kind of start obsessing
over curious little things.

292
00:17:44,419 --> 00:17:46,569
Yeah...

293
00:17:50,309 --> 00:17:53,585
How should I put it...

294
00:17:53,930 --> 00:17:57,530
I thought long and hard about it,

295
00:18:03,546 --> 00:18:06,496
but why do we do that?

296
00:18:07,255 --> 00:18:09,488
Even though we know that...

297
00:18:09,750 --> 00:18:14,090
we won't gain anything
out of that anyhow.

298
00:18:24,039 --> 00:18:27,919
I shouldn't really
be the one talking about this,

299
00:18:30,459 --> 00:18:33,801
but wouldn't making
things simpler solve it?

300
00:18:33,953 --> 00:18:37,053
Like this ochazuke.

301
00:18:41,035 --> 00:18:45,035
There's no need to
make things so complicated.

302
00:18:46,582 --> 00:18:48,981
You like what you like.

303
00:18:49,844 --> 00:18:52,363
Shouldn't that be enough?

304
00:19:00,423 --> 00:19:02,448
Bon apetit.

305
00:20:10,310 --> 00:20:12,240
It's so damn salty!

306
00:20:14,086 --> 00:20:16,016
Are you losing your touch?

307
00:20:16,852 --> 00:20:19,252
Might very well be the case.

308
00:20:21,786 --> 00:20:23,810
Every now and then,

309
00:20:23,866 --> 00:20:27,126
why don't you try
another kind of ochazuke?

310
00:20:29,294 --> 00:20:31,574
On the house.

311
00:20:32,037 --> 00:20:36,407
Like salmon...
or tarako, for instance.

312
00:20:43,061 --> 00:20:45,001
I'll have salmon.

313
00:20:46,117 --> 00:20:47,477
Coming!

314
00:20:50,436 --> 00:20:52,176
Come on in.

315
00:21:00,685 --> 00:21:02,065
Ume ochazuke.

316
00:21:03,273 --> 00:21:04,713
Coming.

317
00:21:20,649 --> 00:21:23,009
I broke up.

318
00:21:23,840 --> 00:21:26,970
I couldn't take him anymore.

319
00:21:27,908 --> 00:21:30,828
What did I tell you?

320
00:21:36,301 --> 00:21:37,851
Here you go.

321
00:21:38,292 --> 00:21:41,052
Ume... and salmon.

322
00:22:05,546 --> 00:22:07,586
Ume's not bad?!

323
00:22:08,533 --> 00:22:10,843
Salmon, too.

324
00:22:17,411 --> 00:22:19,071
Sorry about everything.

325
00:22:20,170 --> 00:22:21,975
Forget about it.

326
00:22:22,296 --> 00:22:25,236
I should...
say the same.

327
00:22:26,592 --> 00:22:28,529
It's just that...

328
00:22:28,726 --> 00:22:30,866
I felt frustrated.

329
00:22:44,364 --> 00:22:45,707
By the way...

330
00:22:45,895 --> 00:22:47,945
Seems like Rumi
is coming back to Tokyo.

331
00:22:48,298 --> 00:22:50,988
Uh?! Really?

332
00:22:51,610 --> 00:22:53,966
Guess her mother recovered...

333
00:22:55,354 --> 00:22:57,852
Or the omiai didn't
go according to plans.

334
00:22:57,876 --> 00:22:59,179
Guess so.

335
00:22:59,480 --> 00:23:02,025
See? You take the easy way out,
and look at what happens.

336
00:23:02,284 --> 00:23:05,207
If it's marriage,
you need them younger.

337
00:23:05,449 --> 00:23:06,270
Right.

338
00:23:06,685 --> 00:23:08,935
You need to experience
that passionate, ardent romance.

339
00:23:09,852 --> 00:23:11,402
Right?!

340
00:23:14,859 --> 00:23:16,489
Tarako!

341
00:23:20,925 --> 00:23:23,715
Tell me, how was the omiai?

342
00:23:23,879 --> 00:23:27,300
- The what?
- Don't act all coy.

343
00:23:27,457 --> 00:23:30,104
<i>Looks like our Ochazuke Sisters...</i>

344
00:23:30,206 --> 00:23:32,049
<i>are back in town.</i>

345
00:23:32,150 --> 00:23:37,205
- What are you prattling about?
- "What are you prattling about?"

346
00:23:38,506 --> 00:23:42,858
~ to be continued ~

347
00:23:42,959 --> 00:23:45,859
Here's your one
point advice for ochazuke.

348
00:23:47,646 --> 00:23:50,638
<i>Only pour the tea or broth
moments before you serve.</i>

349
00:23:50,755 --> 00:23:53,686
<i>Or the rice will get all bloated.</i>

350
00:23:53,873 --> 00:23:56,889
<i>As for the rest,
whichever toppings you prefer.</i>

351
00:23:57,105 --> 00:24:00,775
<i>It's so tasty yet so simple to make,
ochazuke is really great.</i>

352
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:02,384
<i>Right?!</i>

353
00:24:02,710 --> 00:24:06,510
So... Good night everyone!

